    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "see, that's what i'm thinking. it feels less like they're \"rewarding\" me and more like they're trying to buy my silence or just keep me under a microscope. like, if i'm in the corner office, i'm part of the \"inner circle\" and it's harder for me to blow the whistle without looking like a traitor to the firm. have you ever heard of companies using promotions like this to neutralize internal threats?",
